<div class="album-container">

  <!-- Column 1 -->
  <section class="album">
    <h2 style="color: #8c2d55;">Sounds from a Coma</h2>
    <h3>Full Demo Below</h3>
    <iframe width="260" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/5DQM4-cEzSU?si=fX7mkzHitqbKFdep" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>

    <p><span class="cColour italic">Sounds from a Coma</span> is a collection of Eddie Bears All’s earliest songs. They were written between 2015 and 2017 and were performed regularly around music events in Dublin City. Eddie wrote all songs, played every instrument, and mixed them at home from January to May 2025.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Column 2 -->
  <section class="album">
     <h2 style="color: #8c2d55;">Stone Me</h2>
    <h3 style="color: #8c2d55;">(Military Confessions of the Dishonourably Discharged)</h3>

    <p>Cowboy Preacher</p>
    <audio controls>
      <source src="../tps/Cowboy Preacher.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
    </audio>

    <p>Napalm Warfare</p>
    <audio controls>
      <source src="../tps/Napalm Warfare Final.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
    </audio>

    <p><span class="cColour italic">Stone Me</span> is a double album written during Eddie's live performance period before Covid. He has recorded some demos and is currently preparing to re-record the entire album by himself at home.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Column 3 -->
  <section class="album">
     <h2 style="color: #8c2d55;">Neurasthenia</h2>
    <h3>Listen Here</h3>

    <p>Vacant Stare</p>
    <audio controls>
      <source src="../tps/Vacant Stare Final Mix.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
    </audio>

    <p>Misanthropicity’s Lament</p>
    <audio controls>
      <source src="../tps/Misanthropicity's Lament.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
    </audio>

    <p><span class="cColour italic">Neurasthenia</span> was inspired by Eddie’s experiences working in Dublin 1, observing the intense addiction present in the city centre. These songs explore the culture and attitudes of the people he encountered daily.</p>
  </section>

